baseline_groups.claim_summary: IDA program participation (treatment assignment) increases homeownership rates among low-income renters at Wave 4 follow-up.
baseline_groups.notes: Single baseline specification from an RCT. Outcome is homeownership at Wave 4, treatment is random assignment to IDA program. Baseline includes full set of demographic and socioeconomic controls with robust HC1 standard errors. The baseline coefficient is 0.011 (SE=0.039, p=0.77), a null result.

global_notes: This paper has a single core claim (ITT effect of IDA on homeownership). 80 total specifications. Heterogeneity specs (rows 40-50) use interaction terms changing the estimand. Placebo tests (rows 59-63) use different outcome variables. Row 42 (treat x race_cau) has coefficient 0.0 and empty p-value due to no variation in race_cau. Row 39 (LPM no controls) is identical to row 2 (bivariate).
